Package org.trustedcomputinggroup.tnc.ifimc

TCG IF-IMC binding specifications.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AttributeSupport
    These methods can be implemented by an object in the IMC package to get or set attributes.
    IMC
    These methods are implemented by the IMC and called by the TNC Client.
    IMCConnection
    The IMC and TNCC use this IMCConnection object to refer to the network connection when delivering messages and performing other operations relevant to the network connection.
    IMCConnectionLong
    This interface can be implemented by an object that already supports the IMCConnection interface to indicate that this object is an IMCConnection that supports sendMessageLong.
    IMCConnectionSOH
    This interface can be implemented by an object that already supports the IMCConnection interface to indicate that this object is an IMCConnection that supports sendMessageSOH.
    IMCLong
    This interface can be implemented by an object that already supports the IMC interface to indicate that this object is an IMC that supports receiveMessageLong.
    IMCSOH
    This interface can be implemented by an object that already supports the IMC interface to indicate that this object is an IMC that supports functions specific to IF-TNCCS-SOH.
    TNCC
    These methods are implemented by the TNC Client and called by the IMC.
    TNCCLong
    This interface can be implemented by an object that already supports the TNCC interface to indicate that this object is a TNCC that supports reportMethodTypesLong.
    TNCConstants
    A collection of well known or common constants to be used by the IMC and IMV packages.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    TNCException
    An exception that provides information on IF-IMC/IF-IMV errors.
